# QT Collaborative Project: Step-by-Step Task Guide

## 1. Git & Project Setup

1. Install Git and Qt Creator (or preferred IDE).
2. Generate your SSH key:  
   `ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"`
3. Add your public key to GitHub (Settings â†’ SSH and GPG keys).
4. Clone the project repository:  
   `git clone git@github.com:11463144nfu/QT_Course_Plan.git`
5. Configure your Git identity:  
   `git config --global user.name "Your Name"`  
   `git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"`

---

## 2. Joining the Team & Branching

1. Make sure you are added as a collaborator on the GitHub project.
2. Pull the latest changes:  
   `git pull origin main`
3. Create a new branch for your assigned feature:  
   `git checkout -b feature/your-task`
4. Confirm branch creation:  
   `git branch`

---

## 3. Collaborative Coding with Qt & Copilot

1. Open the project in Qt Creator or VS Code.
2. Enable GitHub Copilot extension in your IDE.
3. Start coding your assigned feature or module.
4. Use Copilot to suggest code and UI elements.
5. Discuss design choices and coordinate with teammates.
6. Frequently commit your changes:  
   `git add .`  
   `git commit -m "Add [your feature]"`
7. Push your branch to GitHub:  
   `git push origin feature/your-task`

---

## 4. Integration & Pull Requests

1. After completing your feature, ensure it builds and runs without errors.
2. Go to GitHub and open a Pull Request (PR) from your branch to `main`.
3. Assign teammates for code review.
4. Discuss and resolve any review comments or merge conflicts.
5. Once approved, merge the PR.

---

## 5. Clean-up & Finalization

1. Delete your merged branch on GitHub.
2. On your local machine:  
   `git fetch --prune`  
   `git branch -d feature/your-task`
3. Pull latest changes from `main`:  
   `git pull origin main`

---

## 6. Final Testing & Presentation

1. Run full testing on the integrated project as a team.
2. Prepare a demo showing the teamwork and workflow.
3. Discuss how Git and Copilot facilitated the process.

---

## Reference Links

- [GitHub SSH Key Setup](https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh)
- [Qt Documentation](https://doc.qt.io/)
- [GitHub Copilot](https://github.com/features/copilot)
